venturit.net/?p=591',0,'revision','',0),(592,1,'2013-07-29 13:49:51','2013-07-29 13:49:51','[vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n<h3>Residential Real Estate Development</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.capfund.net/images/pdf/financing_sources/community_econcomic_dev_finance.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Residential Real Estate Development</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Commercial &amp; Mixed Use Development</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.capfund.net/Portals/_Rainbow/Documents/Community%20Econcomic%20Dev%20Finance.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Economic Development Finance Report</a></li>\r\n	<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text]','Financing Sources','','publish','open','open','','financing-sources','','','2013-08-06 18:36:29','2013-08-06 18:36:29','',588,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?page_id=592',0,'page','',0),(593,1,'2013-07-29 13:49:35','2013-07-29 13:49:35','','Financing Sources','','inherit','open','open','','592-revision','','','2013-07-29 13:49:35','2013-07-29 13:49:35','',592,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?p=593',0,'revision','',0),(594,1,'2013-07-29 13:50:26','2013-07-29 13:50:26','','Tax Credits','','publish','open','open','','tax-credits','','','2013-07-29 14:11:41','2013-07-29 14:11:41','',630,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?page_id=594',0,'page','',0),(595,1,'2013-07-29 13:50:23','2013-07-29 13:50:23','','Tax Credits','','inherit','open','open','','594-revision','','','2013-07-29 13:50:23','2013-07-29 13:50:23','',594,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?p=595',0,'revision','',0),(596,1,'2013-07-29 13:51:06','2013-07-29 13:51:06','[vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nAt Great Lakes we are working to create a more simplified \"One Stop\" approach for our clients by offering integrated services that complement our other business lines and products. This division is built on two fundamental concepts—service and expertise. We offer personalized service, and unparalleled expertise. The strength of our underwriters also ensures that your policies are backed by strong financial stability.\r\n\r\nUnder our Real Estate Services division we provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Escrow and title services</li>\r\n	<li>Construction inspection services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo learn more or to request a quote for services, contact Steve Smith (517) 364-8933 or<a href=\"mailto:ssmith@capfund.net\">ssmith@capfund.net</a> .\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text]','Real Estate Services','','publish','open','open','','real-estate-services','','','2013-08-06 18:41:20','2013-08-06 18:41:20','',619,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?page_id=596',0,'page','',0),(597,1,'2013-07-29 13:50:42','2013-07-29 13:50:42','','Services','','inherit','open','open','','596-revision','','','2013-07-29 13:50:42','2013-07-29 13:50:42','',596,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?p=597',0,'revision','',0),(598,1,'2013-07-29 13:51:34','2013-07-29 13:51:34','[vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe Real Estate Organization will explore a number of business opportunities that position properties for future syndication, preserve affordable housing and/or dispose of limited partner interests, and preserve community facilities. This is accomplished through the following initiatives:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Acquire and hold properties for the short-term (under one-year) and long-term (three years or more) based upon strategies unique to each property.</li>\r\n	<li>Find opportunities to partner with non-related development companies to purchase existing projects and serve as a co-General Partner.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop disposition plans for properties that are approaching Year 15.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are a number of LIHTC developments that are nearing the end of their 15-year compliance period. There are also a number of General Partners that would like to sell their interests but are unable to due to the high exit taxes that must be paid upon the sale of these properties. To add to this, declining prices for LIHTC’s has made exiting these developments even more difficult. We will identify these properties and consider acquiring the General Partner interests through a bargain sale, with the ultimate goal of resyndicating the development within one year and preserving the affordable housing. The holding period allows the developer to re-position or finalize take-out financing. These projects will have good cash flow. We may hold some properties for three years or more as circumstances warrant. We will also look at market rate developments in suburban communities with the goal of preserving or providing needed affordable housing in these communities. A number of in-house financing options, such as an acquisition lending program to acquire the interests in these properties are available.\r\n\r\nGLCF will consider investing in non-related development companies. We will evaluate the role that is most beneficial to GLCF and the communities in which we work to determine if our role will be solely as a co-developer or as part of the ownership structure. We have a number of in-house development and financing options at our disposal such as our Pre-Development Lending Program, Triple Bottom Line Funds, NMTC Fund, and LIHTC Funds.\r\n\r\nWe are developing action plans for disposition of LIHTC properties after year 15. Through this analysis, we will have a multitude of options when determining exit strategies.\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact</strong>\r\n\r\nTo learn more about the Great Lakes Real Estate Organization or how we can help you reposition your property, contact:\r\n\r\nKeith Broadnax (608) 260-0050 or <a href=\"mailto:kbroadnax@capfund.net\">kbroadnax@capfund.net</a>\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text]','Real Estate Organization','','publish','open','open','','real-estate-organization','','','2013-08-06 18:42:00','2013-08-06 18:42:00','',619,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?page_id=598',0,'page','',0),(599,1,'2013-07-29 13:51:20','2013-07-29 13:51:20','','Real Estate Organization','','inherit','open','open','','598-revision','','','2013-07-29 13:51:20','2013-07-29 13:51:20','',598,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?p=599',0,'revision','',0),(600,1,'2013-07-29 13:51:49','2013-07-29 13:51:49','[vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nhttps://greatlakes.reportingcentral.net/\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text] [vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nGreat Lakes Capital Fund (GLCF) has been offering <a href=\"http://www.capfund.net/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=141&amp;Itemid=174\">Housing Tax Credit</a> investment opportunities for twenty years. Over the course of these two decades, GLCF has:\r\n\r\n• Consistently met or exceeded the IRR target for every Fund since inception\r\n• Delivered consistent on-time investor reporting\r\n• Never called additional capital from investors above original commitments to save troubled properties\r\n\r\nGLCF offers a variety of Housing Tax Credit investment options. To determine which investment is most suitable for your organization, please contact Marge Novak, VP-Investor relations at (517) 364-8929 or via e-mail at <a href=\"mailto:mnovak@capfund.net\">mnovak@capfund.net</a> .\r\n\r\nFore more information on Housing Tax Credits, please visit <a href=\"http://www.capfund.net/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=141&amp;Itemid=174\">this link</a>.\r\nTo view a listing of Our Investors, please visit <a href=\"http://www.capfund.net/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=69&amp;Itemid=7\">this link</a>.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text]','For The Investor','','publish','open','open','','for-the-investor','','','2013-08-06 18:44:18','2013-08-06 18:44:18','',0,'http://glcf.venturit.net/?page_id=600',