. McDaniel has raised and committed over $2.5 billion of loans and equity for affordable housing, and has diversified the Capital Fund to provide access to permanent debt financing, construction lending, technical assistance, predevelopment lending, youth leadership training, and title services.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text] [vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\"0\" width=\"1/2\" el_position=\"last\"]\r\n\r\nIn addition to his professional experience, Mr. McDaniel has served on the Board of Directors of a number of nonprofit organizations which advocate on behalf of affordable housing, including serving as President of the National Association of State and Local Equity Funds (NASLEF), Board member of Fifth Thirds Community Advisory Forum, Board member of Habitat for Humanity, Treasurer of the Michigan Magnet Fund, Vice Chair of Art of Leadership Foundation, Board member for the Community Economic Development Association of Michigan (CEDAM), member of the Corporation for Supportive Housing State Advisory Committee, Board member of National City Community Development Association, and former Chairman and Board member of the Federal Home Loan Bank of Indianapolis Affordable Housing Council. In 2004 he was the recipient of the Entrepreneur of the Year Award from the Greater Lansing Business Monthly organization, and in 2008 received the Governors Corporate Service Award.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_column] [mk_divider style=\"double_dot\" divider_width=\"full_width\" margin_top=\"20\" margin_bottom=\"20\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [vc_column width=\"1/3\" el_position=\"first last\"] [vc_accordions style=\"fancy-style\" action_style=\"accordion-action\" open_toggle=\"0\" container_bg_color=\"#fff\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [vc_accordion_tab icon=\"\" title=\"Section 1\"] [/vc_accordion_tab] [vc_accordion_tab icon=\"\" title=\"Section 2\"] [vc_column_text disable_pattern=\"true\" align=\"left\" margin_bottom=\